The differences between [puts and print]

[puts] adds a new line & [print] does not:

3.times { print "Hello!" }
# > Hello!Hello!Hello!
 
3.times { puts "Hello!" }
# > Hello!
# > Hello!
# > Hello!

Returning Values:

Code	                   Return Value
"Hello world"	           "Hello world"
6 + 3	                        9
president = "Obama"	       "Obama"
total = 6 + 3	                9
puts "hello world"	         nil
print "hello world"	         nil

Return Values of Method:

def restaurant
  restaurant_name = "Guy's American Kitchen & Bar"
  cuisine = "american"
  motto = "Welcome to Flavor Town!"
end

# using [return]
if you use the [return] method in a [def], it will return that value.